Cynthia Obianodo, the wife of TV host, Ebuka Obi-Uchendu, one of the hosts of the ongoing TV show titled Big Brother Titans, confirmed that her husband is sick. She made the revelation on Sunday, after her husband hosted the BBTitans premiere on Sunday night despite being extremely sick. READ MORE: Why I Committed 2 Abortions At 19, 24 – BBNaija Star, Phyna Spills Meanwhile, some of Ebuka’s fans have started to wish the talented TV host quick recovery. “Okay, noticed he was a bit calm,” Charis Akpabio wrote in the comment section. “Awwww Ebuka. I pray he gets so well soon. His energy was down though,” another commentator also wrote. ‘Big Brother Titans,’ is the biggest version of the Big Brother franchise that Africa has ever seen. The premiere of the show was hosted by Ebuka and South Africa’s Lawrence Maleka on Sunday night. Meanwhile, Both media personalities shared the stage and handled a blend of housemates from different parts of Nigeria and South Africa.